wool waggon
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a large horse or bullock-drawn dray used to transport bales of wool to dump, lighter or wool store.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
